events.name: Golden State Warriors at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton and Pascal Siakam each scored 25 points on Friday night to help the Indiana Pacers race past the Golden State Warriors 108-96.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyrese Haliburton and Pascal Siakam each score 25 to send Pacers past short-handed Warriors 108-96

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 41 points and 14 rebounds and the Milwaukee Bucks beat Orlando 109-106 on Friday night in spite of 34 points by the Magic's Paolo...
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 41 and Bucks hold off Magic 109-106 in Banchero's return

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored 38 points to lead a New Orleans Pelicans team playing without the suspended Zion Williamson past the Philadelphia 76ers 123-115 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: With Williamson suspended, McCollum scores 38 to lead Pelicans past 76ers 123-115

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 23 points and a career-high 28 rebounds and the Sacramento Kings used a fourth quarter rally to beat the Boston Celtics 114-97 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Domantas Sabonis has 23 points and career-high 28 rebounds as Kings rally to beat Celtics 114-97

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 39 points in 29 minutes, and the Oklahoma City Thunder emphatically bounced back to rout the New York Knicks 126-101 on Friday night in the first game since their 15-game winning streak was snapped.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder bounce back to rout Knicks 126-101 in first game since end of 15-game win streak

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 33 points and the Chicago Bulls beat the Washington Wizards 138-105 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine scores 33 points as Bulls beat Wizards 138-105 for 5th win in 7 games

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 35 points, 15 assists and 12 rebounds in his return to the lineup, Russell Westbrook had 25 points, 11 rebounds and 10 assists and the Denver Nuggets beat the Brooklyn Nets 124-105 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Westbrook have triple-doubles and Nuggets beat Nets 124-105
